```java
    WorkerHandle cursorFor(TimelineLedger ledger) {
        TimelineFrame frame = ledger.current();
        if (cursor == null) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        if (!cursor.matches(frame)) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame); // <--- Old cursor is lost and never closed!
            return cursor;
        }

        return cursor;
    }
```

When a `WorkerHandle` is created, it calls `frame.pin()`, which increments the pin count. When `close()` is called on a `WorkerHandle`, it calls `frame.unpin()`. If the pin count never reaches zero (after being 'cooled'), `TimelineFrame` will never call `loadedGeneration.close()`, and the `URLClassLoader` will remain open, leaking Metaspace.

I need to modify `ThreadCache.java` to close the old cursor before replacing it.
